isements, and other images that accompanied James's work, this book reveals the vital interplay of word and image that helped define literary culture at a moment when "popular entertainment" and "high art" had not yet gone their separate ways.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aArt and literaturezUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 0aBooks and readingzUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 0aMagazine illustrationzUnited Statesy19th century. 0aPeriodicalsxPublishingzUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804776233zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804776233423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804776233.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles